
[1]basis

   BA'SIS, n. plu.bases. [L.and Gr.; the same as base, which see.]

   1. The foundation of any thing; that on which a thing stands or lies;
   the bottom or foot of the thing itself, or that on which it rests. See
   a full explanation under base.

   2. The ground work or first principle; that which supports.

   3. Foundation; support.

   The basis of public credit is good faith.

   The basis of all excellence is truth.

   4. Basis, in chimistry. See Base. No. 12.
